  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# GPU vs CPU Accuracy and Performance Comparison\n",
    "This notebook compares the GPU-accelerated Poisson solver against the original CPU implementation. It focuses on the uniform grid case (`azu_unif=2`, `rad_unif=1`) as the nonuniform GPU components are not yet implemented.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will compare:\n",
    "1. **Accuracy**: The L2 relative error of the GPU solver vs. the CPU solver.\n",
    "2. **Performance**: The speedup achieved by using the GPU."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, sys\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import cupy as cp\n",
    "# Main project root\n",
    "repo_root = r\"C:\\Users\\charl\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\NUFFTRR_Poisson\"\n",
    "os.chdir(repo_root)\n",
    "if repo_root not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.append(repo_root)\n",
    "\n",
    "from Tests.CPUvsGPU.helpers import (\n",
    "    run_comparison_pipeline,\n",
    "    render_multitable,\n",
    "    _prepare_table2_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"CuPy is using GPU: {cp.cuda.runtime.getDeviceProperties(0)['name'].decode()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N_vals = [32, 64, 128, 256, 512]\n",
    "M_vals = [32, 64, 128, 256, 512]\n",
    "N_fixed = 32\n",
    "\n",
    "MUTE_OUTPUT = True"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Run Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Running comparison for varying N and M values...\")\n",
    "df_nm = run_comparison_pipeline(N_vals, M_vals, test_type=\"VaryingNM\", mute=MUTE_OUTPUT)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nRunning comparison for varying M, BC, and Quadrature Rule (N fixed at 32)...\")\n",
    "df_bc_quad = run_comparison_pipeline(None, M_vals, test_type=\"VaryingM_BC_Quad\", fixed_val=N_fixed, mute=MUTE_OUTPUT)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDone.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Results: Varying N and M"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "render_multitable(\n",
    "    df_nm,\n",
    "    index_col=\"N\",\n",
    "    columns_col=\"M\",\n",
    "    value_cols=[\"L2_rel_cpu\", \"L2_rel_gpu\", \"accuracy_diff\", \"runtime_cpu\", \"runtime_gpu\", \"speedup\"],\n",
    "    titles=[\"CPU Accuracy (L2 Rel. Error)\", \"GPU Accuracy (L2 Rel. Error)\", \"Accuracy Difference (Abs)\", \n",
    "            \"CPU Runtime (s)\", \"GPU Runtime (s)\", \"Speedup (CPU/GPU)\"],\n",
    "    float_formats=[\n",
    "        lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\",\n",
    "        lambda x: f\"{x:.4f}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.4f}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2f}x\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Results: Varying M, BC, and Quadrature"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_bc_quad_fmt = _prepare_table2_df(df_bc_quad)\n",
    "render_multitable(\n",
    "    df_bc_quad_fmt,\n",
    "    index_col=\"M\",\n",
    "    columns_col=[\"quad_str\", \"bc_str\"],\n",
    "    value_cols=[\"L2_rel_cpu\", \"L2_rel_gpu\", \"accuracy_diff\", \"runtime_cpu\", \"runtime_gpu\", \"speedup\"],\n",
    "    titles=[\"CPU Accuracy (L2 Rel. Error)\", \"GPU Accuracy (L2 Rel. Error)\", \"Accuracy Difference (Abs)\", \n",
    "            \"CPU Runtime (s)\", \"GPU Runtime (s)\", \"Speedup (CPU/GPU)\"],\n",
    "    float_formats=[\n",
    "        lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2e}\",\n",
    "        lambda x: f\"{x:.4f}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.4f}\", lambda x: f\"{x:.2f}x\"\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")"
   ]
  }
